author: Chester Yung
title: Hong Kong Charges Former Leader Donald Tsang With Misconduct
text:
HONG KONG—Former Hong Kong leader Donald Tsang has been charged by the city’s antigraft agency on two counts of misconduct in public office, becoming the most senior official in the former British colony ever to be arrested.
Mr. Tsang, 70, stepped down as Hong Kong’s chief executive in July 2012, but has kept a low profile amid an investigation by the Independent Commission Against Corruption after allegations surfaced in early 2012...
